00:02:23.691 --> 00:02:24.524
so congratulations.

51
00:02:24.524 --> 00:02:31.524
Alright, now let's go over some tips.

52
00:02:31.524 --> 00:02:34.524
Here are some basic tips for your interviewing process.

53
00:02:34.524 --> 00:02:38.678
The interviewer should be an active listener and he

54
00:02:38.678 --> 00:02:40.524
should not interrupt unnecessarily.

55
00:02:40.524 --> 00:02:42.774
The interviewer should be considerate enough.

56
00:02:42.774 --> 00:02:46.524
Even if the interviewer does not agree with the interviewee,

57
00:02:46.524 --> 00:02:48.524
he must respect their feelings, of course.

58
00:02:48.524 --> 00:02:52.524
The interviewer should be friendly and understanding.

59
00:02:52.524 --> 00:02:55.274
He should begin the interview in a friendly manner and try

60
00:02:55.274 --> 00:02:58.191
to make the interviewee just feel a little more relaxed and

61
00:02:58.191 --> 00:02:59.524
a little more comfortable.

62
00:02:59.524 --> 00:03:02.024
The interviewer should keep to the time allotted.

63
00:03:02.024 --> 00:03:05.591
He shouldn't indulge in arguments unnecessarily or debates and things like that.

64
00:03:05.591 --> 00:03:08.524
Don't discuss certain technologies and what might be right or wrong.

65
00:03:08.524 --> 00:03:11.524
Just listen to the answers and move forward.

66
00:03:11.524 --> 00:03:14.337
And the interviewer must be thoroughly prepared for the

67
00:03:14.337 --> 00:03:16.524
questions that are likely to be asked.

68
00:03:16.524 --> 00:03:20.899
He should be a good planner as well, as we've talked about that; plan,

69
00:03:20.899 --> 00:03:21.524
plan, plan.

70
00:03:21.524 --> 00:03:25.524
The interviewer must focus attention on the interviewee.

71
00:03:25.524 --> 00:03:28.524
He should positive gestures when conducting the interview.

72
00:03:28.524 --> 00:03:31.524
Also encourage and invite questions from the interviewee.

73
00:03:31.524 --> 00:03:35.524
Ensure that the interviewee clarifies the question he has and when selected,

74
00:03:35.524 --> 00:03:39.797
a candidate should not feel he is not told about a certain aspect of the job,

75
00:03:39.797 --> 00:03:42.069
so you'll want to make sure that you tell him

76
00:03:42.069 --> 00:03:45.524
everything there is about the job as well.

77
00:03:45.524 --> 00:03:48.191
And avoid any distractions in the interview area.

78
00:03:48.191 --> 00:03:51.191
Ensure that there is no or minimal distraction where

79
00:03:51.191 --> 00:03:52.577
the interview is being conducted.

80
00:03:52.577 --> 00:03:53.103
You know,

81
00:03:53.103 --> 00:03:56.524
a phone ringing all the time in the background can distract both the

82
00:03:56.524 --> 00:04:00.124
interviewer and the interviewee so turn off your cell phone and have

83
00:04:00.124 --> 00:04:02.979
your office phone maybe be on do not disturb.

84
00:04:02.979 --> 00:04:07.524
So try to be in a quiet, nice, comfortable area.

85
00:04:07.524 --> 00:04:10.953
And one more tip of course is if you're not good at

